lines.text: I like the dark. It's friendly.
You cold?
A cat just walked over my grave.
Oh, you can tell Alice anything, she's such a good egg she can understand anything.
There are some things a woman doesn't want other women to understand.
You can fool everybody, but laudie dearie me, you can't fool a cat. They seem to know who's not right.
What should I tell my husband? Naturally, he's anxious to have some word.
What does one tell a husband? One tells him nothing.

[In Serbian]
Moia sestra! Moia sestra!
You're very wise, you know a great deal, yet when you speak of the soul, you mean the mind, and it is not my mind that is troubled.
What a clever girl. All the psychologists have tried for years to find that subtle difference between mind and soul, and you've found it.
Oh, it's alright. It's just that cats don't seem to like me.
Why would she wish to harm you?
Because I'm in love with her husband.
Will you have tea with me in my apartment?
You make everything so simple!
I can't imagine!
Look at that woman over there.
Looks just like a cat.
My goodness, don't nobody like chicken gumbo?
That's Lalage - the perfume I use. I like it, perhaps too well. Maybe I use too much of it, living alone like this.
It's hard to describe. It's not like flowers exactly. It's - it's like something warm and living.

[Looking down at Irena's lifeless body in the form of a panther]
She never lied to us.
